## 🔒 RULE 1 — Inviolable architectural invariants

> **Contracts, not aspirations.** Every commit in this project must respect them. Violations block merge.

### SSOT (Single Source of Truth)
Every piece of knowledge has **exactly one source of truth**. Constants → `config/`. Design tokens → `config/design-tokens.ts`. DB schema → migrations (types generated, not hand-written). Institutional wisdom → `~/.claude/shared/standards/` (stable rules) + `{{cortex_source}}/projects/` (cross-project memory). Current state → this CLAUDE.md. **Zero overlap.**

### Modular (Isolated subsystems)
Features live in `src/features/<slug>/` (or equivalent). External SDKs only via adapters. LEGO tools — one file per tool. No circular imports. Test boundary = module boundary.

### Scalable (10x-safe patterns)
RLS from day 1. Indexes on FK and query predicates. Pagination on all list endpoints. Rate limits + cost guards on external boundaries. Streaming > polling where it makes sense.

**Full contract:** `~/.claude/shared/standards/RULE-1.md`. Anti-patterns there are automatic blockers — not up for debate.

### Rule 2 (Critical): [`security.md`](../.claude/shared/standards/security.md) · [`testing.md`](../.claude/shared/standards/testing.md) · [`observability.md`](../.claude/shared/standards/observability.md) · [`correctness.md`](../.claude/shared/standards/correctness.md)

- **Security** — 8-layer defense + Agentic Security (lethal trifecta, 7 MUST patterns for LLM/agent systems)
- **Testing** — layered pyramid, 5 pillars per test file (happy / error / edge / security / integration)
- **Observability** — structured logs + burn-rate SLOs + circuit breakers + LLM obs stack
- **Correctness** — Zod at boundaries, property-based tests, eval suites for LLM, mutation testing, stateful simulation

### Rule 3 (Process): Performance · A11y · Error · Git · Docs · `~/.claude/shared/standards/ai-patterns.md`

